Debugging in PHP
----------------
1. var_dump()

Dumps(show) information about a variable
example:|||
$message = "hey"
var_dump($message);

OUTPUT:
string(3) "hey"

What I often come across are little helper functions, like this one for instance:
1
2
3
4
5
	
function dump($value) {
    echo ‘<pre>';
    var_dump($value);
    echo ‘</pre>';
}
